## **Step 3: ViewModel Integration for Scheduling/Canceling Reminders**

Integrate reminder scheduling and preference tracking within your HomeViewModel (or wherever you add/update/delete reminders).

You need to:
- Inject the dependencies (`ScheduleReminderUseCase`, `AppPreferences`, and `Context`)
- On add/update: schedule the alarm, and record the ID to prefs
- On delete: cancel the alarm, and remove the ID from prefs

### **Example ViewModel Methods:**

Add these to your `HomeViewModel`:

```kotlin
@HiltViewModel
class HomeViewModel @Inject constructor(
 private val reminderRepository: ReminderRepository,
 private val scheduleReminderUseCase: ScheduleReminderUseCase,
 private val appPreferences: com.app.chronus.prefs.AppPreferences,
 @ApplicationContext private val context: Context
) : ViewModel() {
 // ... existing logic

 fun saveOrUpdateReminder(reminder: Reminder) {
 viewModelScope.launch {
 // Save to Firestore
 if (reminder.id.isEmpty()) {
 reminderRepository.addReminder(reminder)
 } else {
 reminderRepository.updateReminder(reminder)
 }

 // Schedule reminder alarm and persist ID in prefs
 scheduleReminderUseCase.invoke(reminder, context)
 appPreferences.addScheduledReminderId(reminder.id)
 }
 }

 fun deleteReminder(reminder: Reminder) {
 viewModelScope.launch {
 reminderRepository.deleteReminder(reminder.userId, reminder.id)
 scheduleReminderUseCase.scheduler.cancel(reminder, context)
 appPreferences.removeScheduledReminderId(reminder.id)
 }
 }

 // To retrieve scheduled IDs, for example during startup or on boot
 suspend fun getAllScheduledReminderIds(): Set<String> =
 appPreferences.getScheduledReminderIds()
}
```
- This assumes that you receive a complete `Reminder` instance to schedule/cancel.
- Use the above in your Compose flows after add/update/delete.

