Compose’s `AlertDialog` itself limits the dialog width, so even with `fillMaxWidth()` on your calendar, the dialog does not truly go edge-to-edge on phones. To achieve a nearly edge-to-edge (or full width) DatePicker dialog, you must use a custom dialog container using `Dialog`, and then place your own `Surface`/`Card` inside it, controlling the width directly.

**How to fix:** 
- Replace the `AlertDialog` with a custom `Dialog`.
- Inside the dialog, use a `Surface` or `Card` with `Modifier.fillMaxWidth(fraction)` (e.g., `0.98f` for almost full width).
- Add your content (title, DatePicker, confirm button) into that Surface.
- This will give the DatePicker the maximum usable width on all screens.

